replyContent: Thanks for buying the app and supporting the website.Please contact Google Play Store to resolve the download problem. There's nothing I do to make the app not allow multiple downloads. Also, make sure you are logged into the same Google account on both devices.If you can't get it resolved with Google, please contact me at staff@wheresgeorge.com

replyContent: Thanks for your review. I'm not sure what you mean by "not allowing a second use"? There are no such restrictions.  If you do not have a password, please use the "Forgot Password" link on the login page to reset your password. Otherwise, please use "Send Feedback" button to send me a direct note, and I'm sure I can quickly resolve these issues.

I found that after entering 15 bills I could create my profile, which gives you access to a George score which grows as you enter bills and really takes off as you get hits. After 500 bills entered, I got a free one month upgrade to friends of George. Thanks, Hank!

content: SLOW!!!!!!!  Too cumbersome to function correctly. Waisted money on this crap. I end up just using the website.

App is simply just awful. Absolutely frustrating. I will try to explain. Navigating between functions gets you lost in a maze in which you can't seem to get free. For example after entering a SN and clicking done, the app takes you back to the home screen. All the buttons on the home screen are then locked out. Confused I clicked back.  Clicking back gets to back to entering your current bill. But the worst of it is trying this on a second bill. I then am found fighting to figure out how many times I need to click back in order to get "back" to the correct bill. I have found myself "back" on a previously entered bill. Needless to say this makes the app a useless maze of back and forth. Another frustration is it takes up to 3 pictures of a bill, just to get one to be recognized for OCR. Take a picture, approve it. Nope take another picture, approve it, nope take another picture approve it. Finally it takes you to crop the SN. All three pics were perfect, it just wouldn't go to the crop screen.   For a long time I have been anticipating a WG app. I really hope the developers can fix this app. I am using a Nexus 7 2013 edition. Jan 2016.
replyContent: Most other people have no problems using the app on Android.  I'm not sure what your issues are, but the app does work, there are hundreds of people entering hundreds of bills via the app and OCR everyday.
